Repower Advances in Frankfurt on Suzlon’s 63 Million Euro Offer

-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 
2011-07-21T16:41:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/repower-advances-in-frankfurt-on-suzlon-s-63-million-euro-offer.html
Repower Systems SE rose in Frankfurt
trading after Indian parent  Suzlon Energy Ltd. (SUEL)  offered to buy
the 5 percent in the wind turbine maker it doesn’t already own.  Repower rose 13 percent to 143.10 euros by the 5:30 p.m.
close in the city after Suzlon bid 144.77 euros a share, or a
total of about 63 million euros ($91 million), for the unit.  Shareholders will vote on the proposed acquisition at
Hamburg-based Repower’s annual general meeting on Sept. 21,
according to an e-mailed statement today from the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefan Nicola in Berlin at 
